06375nam a22009015i 9783110606416DE-B159720230502090707.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230502t20212022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106064167 a10.1515/97831106064162doi  a(DE-B1597)497233  a(OCoLC)1266228128  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aART0150802bisacsh00aFluctuating Alliances :bArt, Politics, and Diplomacy in the Modern Era /ced. by Pilar Diez del Corral Corredoira. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2021] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (VI, 168 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aContact Zones : Studies in Global Art ,x2196-3746 ;v600tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tFrom a Pact to Rupture and Vice-versa -- tWar and Peace -- tMicro-conflicts and Reputation within Areas of “neutral” Ports during the War of the Spanish Succession -- tIuguntur Iuppiter et Sol -- tFelicitas Duplex -- tJesuits and Diplomacy -- tThe Huron-Wendat Wampum Belt at Chartres -- tRefulgit Sol et Concordia -- tNegotiating with Faith -- tPicturing Politics and Diplomacy -- tA Catholic Crown made of Marble and Paper -- tCourt and Diplomatic Celebrations -- tL’Ambition de l’Espagnol -- tChanging Alliances and their Impact on Charles III of Habsburg’s Royal Music Chapel and its Musicians in Barcelona (1705–1713) -- tAuthors -- tPicture Credits -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWelche Rolle spielten Kunstwerke im Geflecht der rasch wechselnden politischen Allianzen der Frühen Neuzeit? Dieser Frage gehen die interdisziplinären Beiträge des Bandes unter den Blickwinkeln "Krieg und Frieden", "Jesuiten und Diplomatie", "Verhandeln im Namen des Glaubens" und "Höfische und diplomatische Feste" nach. Ein besonderes Augenmerk liegt dabei auf solchen Kunstgattungen, die aufgrund ihrer Reproduzierbarkeit für eine einfache Verbreitung geeignet waren, wie Medaillen und Druckgraphiken. Aber auch Gemälde, Grabmäler und ephemere Inszenierungen wie Feuerwerke dienten der Manifestation von Machtansprüchen. Durch die exemplarischen Analysen entsteht ein breiter Blick auf die politischen Dimensionen des frühneuzeitlichen transkulturellen künstlerischen Austauschs in Europa und darüber hinaus.  aWhat was the role of art in the context of rapidly changing political alliances of the early modern period? The interdisciplinary contributions to this volume explore this question from the perspectives of "War and Peace," "Jesuits and Diplomacy," "Negotiating with Faith," and "Court and Diplomatic Celebrations". Special attention is paid to those art genres that were suitable for easy distribution due to their reproducibility, such as medals and prints. But also paintings, tombs and ephemeral festivities like fireworks served the manifestation of claims to power. The exemplary analyses provide a broad view of the political dimensions of early modern transcultural artistic exchange in Europe and beyond.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aDiplomatie. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aKunst. 4aKunstpolitik. 7aART / History / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aArt, politics, diplomacy, Early Modern.1 aDiez del Corral Corredoira, Pilar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiez del Corral Corredoira, Pilar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGarcía Arenas, Mar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaist, Iris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLipp, Danièle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPuyo, Lise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwartz, Anna Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l